Here's how to handle each scenario with MSTest:

### 1. Windows-only (platform restriction)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
// Or, without a custom attribute:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");

    // ... registry code
}
```

### 2. Skip in CI (environment-based skip)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");

    // ... GPU code
}
```

Then filter in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

### 3. Flaky external API (retry)

```csharp
// MSTest v3.8+ has built-in retry:
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]  // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    var result = CallWeatherApi();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

For older MSTest versions, use a manual loop or a custom attribute.

### 4. Cleanup even on failure (use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`)

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
}

[TestCleanup] // Runs even if the test throws
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void TempFileTest()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
    // ... assertions (cleanup runs regardless of outcome)
}
```

**Key takeaways:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| Platform gate | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or `[OSCondition]` |
| CI skip | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var check |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs) |
